        <type>uint64_t</type>
        <definition>uint64_t MLSpatialAnchorCreateInfo::expiration_timestamp_s</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>expiration_timestamp_s</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>The suggested expiration timestamp for this anchor represented in seconds since the Unix epoch. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This is implemented as an expiration timestamp in the future after which the associated anchor should be considered no longer valid and may be removed by the Spatial Anchor system. If the timestamp is set to zero in this struct, the anchor will never expire. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
